licable policies.\n\nGenerally, electronic information logged is used to gather non-specific demographic information about our visitors and generally such information is used to personalize the information you see displayed on this site. Your IP address may also be used to support and identify your computer so that we can make your visit to our site more enjoyable. Your IP address (or the address of your proxy) may, in certain instances, be linked to personal identifiable information (for example, without limitation, by your request that we store information on certain listings posted on this site or by your use of our messaging services).\n\nWe may use your personal identifying information to send you information about additional offers or services.\u00a0In such cases, we may share your personal and contact information with our team of agents and affiliates to more properly cater the service to you.\n\nWe may use cookies to store information. Cookies are small pieces of information that are stored by your browser on your computer\u2019s hard drive. Cookies are text files that are commonly deposited by sites on a user\u2019s hard drive. The file identifies a user\u2019s computer and can record a user\u2019s preferences and certain other information. Generally, cookies make it easier for you to interact with a site. You may be able to prevent our collection of such data by setting your browser to reject cookies but blocking cookies may adversely affect your ability to interact with this site. You may be able to find your own cookie files on your hard disk and see what information is being stored in such files and by which sites and may be able to delete information contained in such cookie files. To find a cookie file, search for cookie.txt, cookies or MagicCookie.\n\nSecurity\n\nWe use our reasonable efforts to protect the data we collect from you against unauthorized access and we offer the use of a secure socket layer (SSL). A secure socket layer is used to assist in the encryption of information. (You may be able to discern whether your information is being transmitted via SSL by making certain that the Uniform Resource Locator (URL) is prefixed with \u201chttps\u201d rather than \u201chttp\u201d and that a padlock icon is displayed on the lower right corner of your browser (for transmissions via MS Internet Explorer)). If you make a payment through this site, you may be directed to a third party site for payment processing or verification; the policies of such third party site may apply to the processing of your transaction. We are not responsible for the policies of any third party sites.\n\nForum Profile Updates\n\nIf you are a member and have registered with us, we encourage you to update your information as\u00a0it changes. We welcome your updates, questions and comments. Please send e-mails to\u00a0escortforum@bigblackbook.co.za\u00a0and we will promptly respond to your requests.\n\nPrivacy Changes\n\nWhenever we change our privacy policy, we will make reasonable commercial efforts to promptly post a notice on this site indicating that new information has been posted. If at any point we decide to use personally identifiable information in a manner different from that stated at the time it was collected, we will take reasonable commercial efforts to promptly notify you by way of email. To the extent practicable, we will endeavor to offer you a choice as to whether or not we use information previously collected in a different manner. We will take reasonable commercial efforts to use information in accordance with the privacy policy under which the information was collected.\n\nRequired Disclosure of Information\n\nThough we make every effort to preserve your privacy, we may disclose your personal information in certain instances. We will make such disclosure when we believe, in our sole and absolute discretion, that such disclosure or other action is necessary or desirable to comply with applicable law, legal process an